\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Man Student:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Excuse me. Could you hang on a second}{\insrsid1966817 ?}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  I want to mark the courses that will transfer.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Here's a pen.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Man Student:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Oh, thank you. OK . . . Language Development, Sociolinguistics, Psycholinguistics . . . OK.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Now, the Linguistics Department requires two foreign languages. I see you have Spanish. The second language should be one that is not so commonly used.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Man Student:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  What about the courses I've taken in American }{\insrsid14827227\charrsid4012400 Sign}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Language? We had to b
e fluent in signing in order to communicate with people who have hearing disabilities.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  I'm not sure if we can count your sign language courses, and at this point I'd rather err on the side of caution and tell you that it doesn't fulfill t
he requirement.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Man Student:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  That seems reasonable. So Spanish will transfer - and I'll put a question mark beside the American Sign Language courses.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Hmmm. Well, just at a glance, I would say that this change of major may only set you back by a semester or two.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Man Student:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Are you calculating that based on the average number of classes that students take per term?
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Well, yes. Would graduating later be a problem?
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Man Student:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  It might be.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  I suppose th
at if you were to carry a heavier course load, you might be able to finish on schedule. But since some of the higher level courses have prerequisites, your taking on more courses per semester may not necessarily enable you to graduate as soon as you'd lik
e.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Man Student:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  Well, I need to look into all options. I might be able to get more funding.
\par }{\insrsid14827227 
\par }{\b\insrsid14827227\charrsid14827227 Woman Professor:}{\insrsid14827227\charrsid8943298  OK. Well, why don't you take the overview I gave you and continue crossing out the courses you won't have to take. Then check the courses that you
